  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zambia Accountability Programme (ZAP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ZAP aims to strengthen supply and demand-led mechanisms of accountability to deliver improvements in the lives of Zambia&#x2019;s poor, particularly in relation to service delivery. Specifically, programme interventions include strengthening political processes and democratic institutions; Improving access to education for vulnerable girls through a bursary programme, and strengthening school governance structures to facilitate policy implementation and institutionalise accountability mechanisms; and Increasing the capacity of local think tanks to carry out politically informed, high quality research and build partnerships to influence economic policy.</narrative>
  </description>
